channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Questions surround weapon, motive in deadly Georgia high school shooting
item.description: Four people were killed in a shooting at Apalachee High School in Winder, Georgia, on Wednesday morning, according to authorities.

item.title: Newly Spotted Asteroid Burns Up Over Philippines
What we know about the Georgia high school shooting suspect
item.description: The teen accused of killing four people at Apalachee High School was interviewed after the FBI received anonymous tips in 2023 about online threats, the agency said.

item.title: Rape trial in France to hear of woman's decade-long ordeal of drugging and abuse
item.description: A woman who was allegedly drugged by her now ex-husband so that she could be raped while unconscious by other men is testifying in a court in France about her yearslong ordeal

item.title: Georgia school shooter suspected of killing two teachers was interviewed by FBI
Police exchange fire with armed man near Israeli Consulate in Munich
item.description: Police in Munich, Germany exchanged fire with a gunman near the Israeli Consulate and a museum on Nazi-era history, leaving the suspect wounded.

item.title: Trump asks federal appeals court for stay in hush money case sentencing
item.description: Donald Trump has asked a federal appeals court for a stay that would delay the sentencing in his New York hush-money case, which is scheduled for Sept. 18.

item.title: State 54 to close for construction starting Monday; State 47 to close later this month
Jury selection for Hunter Biden's tax evasion trial to begin in Los Angeles
item.description: The president's son, accused of failing to pay at least $1.4 million in federal taxes while living an "extravagant lifestyle," is on trial for the second time this year.

item.title: Munich police shoot gunman dead amid 'major' operation in city center
item.description: Munich police shot dead a "suspicious person" in the Karolinenplatz area of the southern German city on Thursday morning, authorities said.

item.title: Russian firms bought spare parts for 25-year-old ASML machines, says newspaper Trouw
At least 118 eagles killed by trafficking ring, prosecutors say
item.description: A man helped kill at least 118 eagles to sell their feathers and body parts on the black market as part of a long-running wildlife trafficking ring in the western U.S. that allegedly killed thousands of birds, court filings show.

item.title: Ugandan Olympic athlete dies after being severely burned by her partner
item.description: Ugandan Olympic athlete Rebecca Cheptegei has died at a Kenyan hospital where she was being treated for burns over 80% of her body from an attack by her partner

item.title: 3 High-Yield Dividend Stocks to Buy Sooner Rather Than Later
Ugandan Olympian dies after allegedly being set on fire by boyfriend
item.description: Officials in Uganda say Olympic runner Rebecca Cheptegei has died in a Kenyan hospital four days after she was allegedly set on fire by her boyfriend.
